      "contentBlocks": [
        "The Gerontology Department offers advising to current Gerontology majors and minors as well as anyone interested in learning more about studying Gerontology at Sacramento State.",
        "If you are a current Sac State student, click here to schedule an advising appointment through EAB .",
        "Current and future students can email ssis-gero-sc@csus.edu to schedule an advising session with a Gerontology faculty member. Please email at least 48 hours in advance and let us know a few days and times that work for you as well as whether you would like to meet in person or virtually.",
        "Current and future students can also pop into an open virtual advising session most Mondays from 5-6pm . Zoom: https://csus.zoom.us/j/2507778940",
        "Current majors and minors meet with a Gerontology advisor every semester to make sure they are on track to complete their degree. We help students select courses, find practicum placements, connect with supportive services, apply for graduation, and explore graduate school and career opportunities.",
        "Whether you are already a Sacramento State student or thinking about coming to Sacramento State, we would be happy to visit with you about the Gerontology degree options. A Gerontology faculty member can review the courses you have already taken, if any, and help you decide if Gerontology would be a good fit for you as a major or minor. We can also help you declare your degree when you are ready."
      ],
